This paper deals with privacy-preserving routing optimization in Software Defined Networking (SDN) environments. It involves the use of cryptographic protocols to protect the private information of domains. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also deals with network optimization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper deals with large-scale enterprise networks and data center networks, which could place it in cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper involves the use of mathematical proofs to guarantee privacy, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory).
